I have seen five specimens of the typical form of this species, all from Mexico—two males in the Salle collection, a female in the Baly collection, and a pair in the British Museum. The description of Boheman 1 was taken from the male sex only ; the female is ovate, and much more elongate, with less expanded elytral margins, the male being rotundate, with the margins of the elytra broadly expanded‚ and abruptly and obliquely converging at the base.
